            <abstract xml:lang="en">Inverse problems occur in a wide range of scientific applications, such as in the fields of signal processing, medical imaging, or geophysics. This work aims to present to the field practitioners, in an accessible and concise way, several established and newer cutting-edge computational methods used in the field of inverse problems—and when and how these techniques should be employed.</abstract>
